1. Install any code editor in your system
    for example - VS code, sublime text, apache netbeans, etc
    

2. Install Node.js and npm in your system
   link - https://nodejs.org/en/download/prebuilt-installer
   after installing check its versions
   node -v # should print `v20.18.0`
   npm -v # should print `10.8.2`

3.Extract the zip folder and open it in code editor as open folder,
    The file structure should be like this,
    ONLINE-JAVA-COMPILER - SINGLE VERSION
    ├── public
    │   └── index.html
    ├── temp
    │   ├── file4.class
    │   └── file4.java
    ├── .gitignore
    ├── package-lock.json
    ├── package.json
    ├── readme
    ├── README.md
    └── server.js

4. Install dependencies:
   npm install express cors

   Once you install the dependencies, the file structure will be-
   ONLINE-JAVA-COMPILER - SINGLE VERSION
    ├── node_modules
    ├── public
    │   └── index.html
    ├── temp
    │   ├── file4.class
    │   └── file4.java
    ├── .gitignore
    ├── package-lock.json
    ├── package.json
    ├── readme
    ├── README.md
    └── server.js

5. Save the codes with ctrl+s


6. Run the server:
    Write the command in terminal-
    node server.js

7. This link will be active then, click the link or copy the link and paste it in any of your browser
    http://localhost:3000/

8. Write the code in the editor and click on compile and run button,
   the result will be shown in the output section.

9. Until the node server is running in the terminal, you use the website,
    to stop the server press ctrl+c in the terminal.

10. To run the server again, write the command in terminal-
    node server.js

11. The server will be running again and the website will be active again.
